 galego-portugiesische cantigas, mittellateinische Beispiele sowie Texte der scuola siciliana versammelt.  aThis study is a significant contribution to our understanding of the structures of lyric poetry in the Middle Ages. The book discusses the Tagelied and the often overlooked Romance dream poem, focusing on erotic variants and their poetic treatment. This anthology of Romance alba and somni poetry also includes the verse of troubadours and trouvères, Galician-Portuguese cantigas, Middle Latin selections, and texts from the scuola siciliana. Original German translations provide a basis for comparative analysis.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aDreams in literature. 0aLove poetry, Romance-languagexHistory and criticism. 0aPoetry, MedievalxHistory and criticism. 4aLyrik/Mittelalter. 4aRomania. 4aTagelied. 4aTraum. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aDawn Song.  aDream Poetry.  aLatin Europe.  aMiddle Ages.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2012z9783110288896oZDB-23-DGA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET MEDIÄVISTIK 2010-2012z97831103011680 cprintz978311025946940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311027514840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110275148423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110275148/original  a978-3-11-030116-8  E-BOOK PAKET MEDIÄVISTIK 2010-2012c2010d2012  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA